The minor was raped after armed robbers attacked her parents’ home and tied up other family members. Daily Trust reported that a health worker at the Kubwa General Hospital, who pleaded for anonymity, confirmed the development. She is said to be suffering from an unusual v*ginal discharge, pain in her lower abdomen and pain when urinating since the incident. The health worker added;

“The victim hasn’t been responding to treatment and her family has spent a lot of money. I learnt that she would soon be referred to the University of Abuja Teaching Hospital (UATH), Gwagwalada.”